<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="46" type="reference_group">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,701,1400]" pageId="1" pageNumber="46">
<taxonomicName box="[199,386,1129,1153]" class="Insecta" family="Muscidae" genus="Brachygasterina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="46" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[199,386,1129,1153]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="46">Brachygasterina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has been examined in recent literature, with a comprehensive redescription of the genus, descriptions of species and a key to the species (de 
<bibRefCitation author="Carvalho" box="[723,978,1164,1188]" pageId="1" pageNumber="46" refString="de Carvalho, C. J. B &amp; Pont, A. C. (2006) Taxonomy, cladistics and biogeography of the South American genus Brachygasterina Macquart (Diptera: Muscidae). Zootaxa, 1151, 1 - 26." type="journal article" year="2006">
Carvalho &amp; Pont 
<number box="[919,978,1164,1188]" pageId="1" pageNumber="46" value="2006.0">2006</number>
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Couri" box="[988,1179,1164,1189]" pageId="1" pageNumber="46" refString="Couri, M. S., de Carvalho, C. J. B. &amp; Pont, A. C. (2007) A new species of Brachygasterina Macquart from Chile (Diptera, Muscidae, Azeliinae). Neotropical Entomology, 36, 229 - 232." type="journal article" year="2007">
Couri 
<emphasis box="[1059,1115,1165,1189]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="46">et al.</emphasis>
<number box="[1120,1179,1164,1188]" pageId="1" pageNumber="46" value="2007.0">2007</number>
</bibRefCitation>
, Soares &amp; de Carvalho 
<number box="[151,212,1199,1223]" pageId="1" pageNumber="46" value="2007.0">2007</number>
). The genus was recently included in a cladistic analysis of Reinwardtiinae (
<emphasis box="[1115,1177,1201,1224]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="46">sensu</emphasis>
Couri &amp; de 
<bibRefCitation author="Carvalho" pageId="1" pageNumber="46" refString="Couri, M. S. &amp; de Carvalho, C. J. B. (2003) Systematic relations among Philornis Meinert, Passeromyia Rodhain &amp; Villeneuve and allied genera (Diptera, Muscidae). Brazilian Journal of Biology, 63, 223 - 232." type="journal article" year="2003">
Carvalho 
<number box="[151,211,1235,1259]" pageId="1" pageNumber="46" value="2003.0">2003</number>
</bibRefCitation>
), within the doctoral thesis of Elaine D.G. Soares. As understood in the present paper, 
<taxonomicName box="[1180,1367,1235,1259]" class="Insecta" family="Muscidae" genus="Brachygasterina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="46" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1180,1367,1235,1259]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="46">Brachygasterina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is not a monophyletic group and the cladistic analysis of 
<bibRefCitation author="Soares" box="[743,902,1270,1294]" pageId="1" pageNumber="46" refString="Soares, E. D. G. (2008) Reinwardtiinae (Diptera: Muscidae) e um grupo monofiletico?: uma abordagem cladistica morfologica e molecular. Ph. D. Thesis, Programa de Pos-graduacao em Entomologia, Universidade Federal do Parana, Curitiba. 160 pp." type="book" year="2008">
Soares (
<number box="[835,894,1270,1294]" pageId="1" pageNumber="46" value="2008.0">2008</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
suggests a new taxonomic arrangement along with the other Andean genera 
<taxonomicName authority="Malloch, Dalcyella Carvalho" authorityName="Malloch, Dalcyella Carvalho" box="[506,986,1305,1329]" class="Insecta" family="Muscidae" genus="Correntosia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="46" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[506,640,1306,1329]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="46">Correntosia</emphasis>
Malloch, 
<emphasis box="[761,870,1305,1329]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="46">Dalcyella</emphasis>
Carvalho
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Rondani" authorityName="Rondani" box="[1000,1243,1305,1329]" class="Insecta" family="Muscidae" genus="Palpibracus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="46" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1000,1137,1305,1329]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="46">Palpibracus</emphasis>
Rondani
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Stein. Today" authorityName="Stein. Today" class="Insecta" family="Muscidae" genus="Psilochaeta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="46" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1303,1435,1305,1329]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="46">Psilochaeta</emphasis>
Stein. Today
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[304,490,1341,1365]" class="Insecta" family="Muscidae" genus="Brachygasterina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="46" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[304,490,1341,1365]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="46">Brachygasterina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
comprises 
<number box="[619,646,1340,1364]" pageId="1" pageNumber="46" value="11.0">11</number>
species (including the new species described herein), six of which are found at higher altitudes in 
<collectingCountry box="[459,554,1375,1399]" name="Ecuador" pageId="1" pageNumber="46">Ecuador</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[566,676,1375,1399]" name="Colombia" pageId="1" pageNumber="46">Colombia</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[730,849,1375,1399]" name="Venezuela" pageId="1" pageNumber="46">Venezuela</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
